saveHInstColor(25.10)                                    saveHInstColor(25.10)

Name
       saveHInstColor - Saves the current color setting for a hierarchical in-
       stance from the Module Color Preference form to a file

Syntax
       saveHInstColor

       [-help]

       <fileName>

       Saves  the  current  color setting for a hierarchical instance from the
       Module Color Preference form to a file.  The  Module  Color  Preference
       form is accessed by clicking Floorplan - Edit Floorplan - Color Module.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each saveHInstColor parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man saveHInstColor.

       <fileName>
              Specifies  the  name  of  the file that stores 30 color settings
              starting with the setLayerPreference command.

              This is the same behavior as the Save button on the Module Color
              Preference form.

Example
       The following command saves the current color setting for a  hierarchi-
       cal instance from the Module Color Preference form to a file named hin-
       stColorFile:

       saveHInstColor hinstColorFile

